The paper focuses on generating face images using GANs, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training the discriminator using a margin-based ranking loss, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of different GAN approaches and compares their performance, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper involves visual improvements in face generation, which could be related to computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves generating and completing face images, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
